abstract: Days before it leaves the European Union, Britain put itself at odds with European allies on Wednesday in warmly welcoming U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan while France and the wider EU warned that it must respect international law.
snippet: Days before it leaves the European Union, Britain put itself at odds with European allies on Wednesday in warmly welcoming U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan while France and the wider EU warned that it must respect international...
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Days before it leaves the European Union, Britain put itself at odds with European allies on Wednesday in warmly welcoming U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan while France and the wider EU warned that it must respect international law.
headline_main: Gaps Emerge Between Britain and EU Over Trump Middle East Plan
headline_print_headline: Gaps Emerge Between Britain and EU Over Trump Middle East Plan

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday proposed the creation of a Palestinian state with a capital on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday proposed the creation of a Palestinian state with a capital on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday proposed the creation of a Palestinian state with a capital on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
headline_main: Factbox: U.S. Middle East Peace Plan Prompts Some Praise, Much Arab Anger
headline_print_headline: Factbox: U.S. Middle East Peace Plan Prompts Some Praise, Much Arab Anger

abstract: Saudi Arabia's King Salman reassured the Kingdom's commitment to the Palestinian issue and Palestinian rights, in a phone call with Palestinian president Mahmoud Abbas, the Saudi state news agency reported early on Wednesday.
snippet: Saudi Arabia's King Salman reassured the Kingdom's commitment to the Palestinian issue and Palestinian rights, in a phone call with Palestinian president Mahmoud Abbas, the Saudi state news agency reported early on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: CAIRO — Saudi Arabia's King Salman reassured the Kingdom's commitment to the Palestinian issue and Palestinian rights, in a phone call with Palestinian president Mahmoud Abbas, the Saudi state news agency reported early on Wednesday.
headline_main: King Salman Reassures Saudi Arabia's Commitment to the Palestinian Issue
headline_print_headline: King Salman Reassures Saudi Arabia's Commitment to the Palestinian Issue

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson said on Wednesday no Middle East peace plan was perfect, but the one put forward by U.S. President Donald Trump had the merit of being a two-state solution and should be considered by Palestinian leaders.

lead_paragraph: LONDON — British Prime Minister Boris Johnson said on Wednesday no Middle East peace plan was perfect, but the one put forward by U.S. President Donald Trump had the merit of being a two-state solution and should be considered by Palestinian leaders.

abstract: Israel's hawkish defense minister called on Wednesday for Israel to establish sovereignty over nearly a third of the occupied West Bank, acting on U.S. President Donald Trump's announcement of a Middle East peace plan that Palestinians branded apartheid.

lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Israel's hawkish defense minister called on Wednesday for Israel to establish sovereignty over nearly a third of the occupied West Bank, acting on U.S. President Donald Trump's announcement of a Middle East peace plan that Palestinians branded apartheid.
headline_main: Citing Trump Plan, Israel Defense Chief Backs Extending Sovereignty to West Bank Settlements
headline_print_headline: Citing Trump Plan, Israel Defense Chief Backs Extending Sovereignty to West Bank Settlements

abstract: Lev Parnas, an indicted businessman who says he worked to pressure Ukraine to investigate one of President Donald Trump's political rivals, traveled to Washington to press the Senate to allow him to testify in Trump's impeachment trial, only to be turned away at the U.S. Capitol.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lev Parnas, an indicted businessman who says he worked to pressure Ukraine to investigate one of President Donald Trump's political rivals, traveled to Washington to press the Senate to allow him to testify in Trump's impeachment trial, only to be turned away at the U.S. Capitol.
headline_main: Parnas, Former Ukraine Fixer, Turned Away From Trump Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: Parnas, Former Ukraine Fixer, Turned Away From Trump Impeachment Trial

abstract: Mexican President Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador said on Wednesday  "we don't want to fight", responding to reports that U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday repeated his claim that Mexico is paying for a border wall, adding that elections are approaching in the United States.
snippet: Mexican President Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador said on Wednesday  "we don't want to fight", responding to reports that U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday repeated his claim that Mexico is paying for a border wall, adding that elections are appr...
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Mexican President Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador said on Wednesday "we don't want to fight", responding to reports that U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday repeated his claim that Mexico is paying for a border wall, adding that elections are approaching in the United States.

headline_print_headline: Mexican President Says 'We Don't Want to Fight' After Trump Repeats Border Wall Claim

abstract: The United States hopes to discuss the entire strategic framework of its relationship with Iraq soon, a U.S. envoy said on Tuesday, as the fate of a U.S. military mission there remains in doubt after a drone strike that killed an Iranian general.
snippet: The United States hopes to discuss the entire strategic framework of its relationship with Iraq soon, a U.S. envoy said on Tuesday, as the fate of a U.S. military mission there remains in doubt after a drone strike that killed an Iranian general.
lead_paragraph: COPENHAGEN — The United States hopes to discuss the entire strategic framework of its relationship with Iraq soon, a U.S. envoy said on Tuesday, as the fate of a U.S. military mission there remains in doubt after a drone strike that killed an Iranian general.
headline_main: U.S. Hopes to Discuss 'Entire Strategic Framework' With Iraq Soon
headline_print_headline: U.S. Hopes to Discuss 'Entire Strategic Framework' With Iraq Soon

abstract: A U.S. proposal for Israeli-Palestinian peace does not call for imposing any change to prayer arrangements around a key Jerusalem mosque compound which was also the site of ancient Jewish temples, a U.S. official said on Wednesday.
snippet: A U.S. proposal for Israeli-Palestinian peace does not call for imposing any change to prayer arrangements around a key Jerusalem mosque compound which was also the site of ancient Jewish temples, a U.S. official said on Wednesday.

headline_main: U.S. Sees No Imposed Change to 'Status Quo' Around Al-Aqsa Mosque
